The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of graph constraint logic, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The authors also mention the use of Rush Hour, a popular puzzle game, as a tool for their complexity analysis, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the study of treewidth and maximum degree of graphs, which are common topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT).
